&gt;modularity is one that I haven&#39;t considered so much.  I have considered a 
&gt;plan where nested data structures use multiple fIDs to identify the 
&gt;separate parts.  e.g. if we have something roughtly equivalent to:
&gt;
&gt;struct Coord {
&gt;         float x;
&gt;         float y;
&gt;         float z;
&gt;};
&gt;
&gt;         Then a fID on the outer item (the Coord) identifies it as a 
&gt;coordinate, and separate fIDs on the x, y and z identify them.
&gt;
